    {
      "parameters": {
        "method": "POST",
        "url": "https://api.groq.com/openai/v1/chat/completions",
        "authentication": "genericCredentialType",
        "genericAuthType": "httpHeaderAuth",
        "sendBody": true,
        "specifyBody": "json",
        "jsonBody": "={\n  \"model\": \"llama-3.3-70b-versatile\",\n  \"messages\": [\n    {\n      \"role\": \"user\",\n      \"content\": \"You are an expert B2B sales development representative. Write a concise, highly personalized email.\\n\\n<lead_data>\\nCompany: {{ $('Webhook').item.json.body.lead.companyName }}\\nRating: {{ $('Webhook').item.json.body.lead.googleRating }}\\nIndustry/Type: {{ $('Webhook').item.json.body.lead.googleTypes }}\\n</lead_data>\\n\\n<instructions>\\n{{ $('Webhook').item.json.body.userPrompt }}\\n</instructions>\\n\\nSTRICT RULES:\\n1. MISSING DATA: If any data point in <lead_data> is blank, empty, \\\"null\\\", or missing (like the rating or industry), DO NOT bring it up. Do not guess it. Ignore it completely.\\n2. NO PLACEHOLDERS: You are strictly forbidden from using bracketed placeholders like [Name], [Lead Name], [Company], or [Your Name].\\n3. GREETING: If you do not have a specific contact name, use a general professional greeting like \\\"Dear Team at {{ $('Webhook').item.json.body.lead.companyName }},\\\" or just \\\"Hello,\\\".\\n4. SIGN-OFF: End the email professionally, but do not use a placeholder for the sender's name. Just end it with \\\"Best regards,\\\" or similar.\\n5. FORMAT: Use HTML <br> tags for line breaks.\\n\\nOUTPUT EXACTLY THIS JSON AND NOTHING ELSE:\\n{\\n  \\\"subject\\\": \\\"Your generated subject\\\",\\n  \\\"body\\\": \\\"Your generated body\\\"\\n}\"\n    }\n  ]\n}",
        "options": {}
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.httpRequest",
      "typeVersion": 4.2,
      "position": [
        -960,
        128
      ],
      "id": "b54eda6e-c292-42cd-aab3-8fed80c72885",
      "name": "Message a model",
      "credentials": {
